    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-27T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-27T10:00:00-05:00" n="183"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/3453: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-27T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 27, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:13 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>693. Embassy’s 319, January 13, 4 p.m. Foreign Office has written to the Embassy
                    regarding the substance of the last sentence of the antepenultimate paragraph of
                    the telegram under reference. Foreign Office has now heard from the British
                    Minister in Stockholm<note n="82" xml:id="d183fn82">V. A. L. Mallet.</note> that
                    the Swedish Government is informing the Axis Governments that it assumes that
                    the latter will provide bunkers at the Piraeus for their [<hi rend="italic"
                        >the?</hi>] vessel while it is in Greek waters. The British Minister added
                    that the alternative would be the periodical transfer of oil from the bunkers of
                    ships arriving from Canada,; and the Minister has asked what would be the
                    attitude of the United States and British Governments if the Axis should refuse
                    to provide these bunkers.</p>
                <p>Foreign Office has replied to the Minister that it considers that the Axis should
                    provide these bunkers in Greece and that it does not wish to prejudge its
                    attitude in the event of Axis refusal.</p>
                <p>Foreign Office has requested our views on the point raised. Please advise.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Matthews</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
